---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Caption
description: a caption for a figure (or table)
---

{% from "components/caption/macro.njk" import caption %}

<h2>With a figure</h2>
<figure>
  <div style="background: var(--nhsuk-pale-grey); padding: var(--nhsuk-spacing-5); text-align: center;">
    [figure placeholder]
  </div>
  {{ caption({
    text: "Figure 1 — Measles incidence in England, 2010 – 2024."
  }) }}
</figure>

<h2>With rich content</h2>
<figure>
  <div style="background: var(--nhsuk-pale-grey); padding: var(--nhsuk-spacing-5); text-align: center;">
    [chart placeholder]
  </div>
  {% call caption() %}
    <strong>Figure 2</strong> — Source: <a href="#">ONS 2024 health dataset</a>.
  {% endcall %}
</figure>

<h2>Table caption</h2>
<p>For tables, prefer the <a href="/components/table/">Table macro</a>'s
  <code>caption</code> parameter so the <code>&lt;caption&gt;</code>
  element appears at the top of the table as HTML requires. The
  standalone Caption macro can emit a <code>&lt;caption&gt;</code>
  via <code>params.as: "caption"</code> when that composition is
  unavailable.</p>
